The paper focuses on constructing structured queries for knowledge graphs using natural language questions, which involves techniques from artificial intelligence (cs.AI), databases (cs.DB), computational linguistics (cs.CL), machine learning (cs.LG), and information retrieval (cs.IR). Therefore, these five sub-categories are the most likely candidates for this paper.
